<br>
It's your life. Do use, or discard as you see fit. There is an unfortunate radius effect of your life (or death) on others, but at some point, you have to consider yourself first. <br>
<br>
It's no different than people who stay in loveless or abusive relationships because they feel an obligation to another (usually children of the relationship). The result of this is often more damageing to the people who were supposed to be 'spared' pain. <br>
<br>
Which do you think would hurt more, a sudden lose of someone you cared about; or a long, slow process of watching them suffer and grow more and more miserable?<br>
<br>
Sometimes, ifyou really care about someone, you have to let them go. Demanding they remain just so you don't have to feel bad is selfish, and cruel.<br>
